The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Wednesday, March 17, 2004 				 																				TAPAS PAL								Actor																																							The trend of showbiz people campaigning for or contesting the elections has its merits and demerits. But film stars certainly do leave a mark on the crowd. Their ardent fans most often like to side with the parties they are pitching in for. But politics is not everybodys cup of tea. Though one doesnt have to attend classes on politics to be a politician, one has to be able to judge the good from the bad in order to serve the people.
